<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 5:47PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southwestern Summers and Mercer Counties through 615 PM EDT...
At 547 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sandlick, or near Bluefield, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Princeton...
Athens...
Matoaka...
Pipestem...
Camp Creek...
and Bramwell.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
